SIMPLE: withdraw
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Withdraw
<hw>With*draw"</hw> <pr>(w⟦icr⟧⟦th⟧*dr⟦add⟧")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Withdrew</conjf> <pr>(-dr⟦udd⟧")</pr>;
<pos>p. p.</pos> <conjf>Withdrawn</conjf> <pr>(-dr⟦add⟧n")</pr>; <pos>p.
pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Withdrawing</conjf>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[<ets>With</ets> against + <ets>draw.</ets>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To take back or away, as what has been bestowed or enjoyed; to draw
back; to cause to move away or retire; <as>as, to <ex>withdraw</ex> aid,
favor, capital, or the like</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Impossible it is that God should <qex>withdraw</qex> his presence
from anything.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To take back; to recall or retract; <as>as, to
<ex>withdraw</ex> false charges</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Withdraw</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Withdraw
<hw>With*draw"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To retire; to retreat; to
quit a company or place; to go away; <as>as, he <ex>withdrew</ex> from
the company</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧When the sea <xex>withdrew</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>King Horn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To recede; retrograde; go back.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Withdrawal</ent>⟦br⟧
